    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-10-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-12-11T22:58:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Daniel Pearl Freedom of the Press Act of 2009 - Amends the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to require inclusion of specified freedom of the press information in the Department of State's annual Country Reports on Human Rights Practices.</p> <p>Directs the Secretary to administer a grant program to promote freedom of the press worldwide, which shall be administered by the Department's Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights and Labor. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>36</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-12-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed House amended</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-03-26T19:36:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Daniel Pearl Freedom of the Press Act of 2009 - Amends the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to expand the annual Country Reports on Human Rights Practices to include: (1) a description of the status of freedom of the press in each country reviewed in the report; (2) identification of countries in which there were violations of freedom of the press; and (3) in countries where there are particularly severe violations of freedom of the press, whether such governments participate in or condone such violations and the actions such governments have taken to preserve the safety and independence of the media and ensure the prosecution of individuals who attack or murder journalists.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
